        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Norton Commons, moving east-northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lyndon, Middletown, Douglass Hills, Prospect, Hurstbourne, Anchorage,
Worthington Hills, Barbourmeade, Coldstream, and Rolling Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
